data.title: Flying High the History of the Essendon Football Club
data.meta_description: Flying High. The History Of The Essendon Football Club. by MAPLESTONE, MICHAEL. and a great selection of related books, art and collectibles available now at AbeBooks.com.
data.text:
First Edition; Cr. 4to; pp. 329; 16 b/w illustrations; stiff illustrated wrapper, wrapper slightly bumped and creased, a good copy. Includes interesting information on a football game between Collingwood and Essendon on the fifth of July 1862, and the 1858 match with the goals a mile apart. Includes full page b/w illustrations of Graham Moss, premiers 1897, 1901, 1911, 1912, 1923. 1924, 1942, 1946, 1949, 1950, 1962, 1965 also VFA records from 1877 and Statistics Year by Year from 1897 and Essendon's complete year by year since 1897 listing team members, and more.

Soft cover. Condition: Fine. 1st Edition. 329pp. Pictorial col. illust. covers, b/w full page plts., tables, lists, charts. Light creasing to covers. Essendon Football Club is now one hundred and twelve years old. For generations it has faithfully served its thousands of devoted followers. It has made men who have worn its red and black colours famous. It has developed into a cult following. The club has never been adversley affected by coming into existence a little latter than some other clubs. It had the distinction of winning four consecutive Victorian Football League premiership in 1897. Since then Essendon has always been one of the foremost clubs in football. Size: Quarto. Book.
